description: Sergio Aragones, master cartoonist, tells the classic tale of the kindly old toymaker who wanted more than anything in the world a son - and a wife! Sergio will also delight you with the other love of his youth (besides cartooning) - marionette puppets. Also, there will be plenty of puns and puzzles to please and perplex you.

The loving, affectionate parody that skewers one of the greatest science fiction franchises of all time continues! In the tradition of Robot Chicken: Star Wars and Spaceballs, join the unlikely band of travelers as they find themselves in quite a pickle in Lord Salvadore's grasp! Will they escape in time to stop the Dread Lord's plans?
name: "It was a Dark Time for the Kingdom..."

description: A group of new villains under the command of Fire Lord attack a fueling station. Alpha team tries to stop them, but is forced to retreat. Now the heroes have only one option left - to try the new experimental technology called "upgrade".
name: Ordeal of Fire

description: Rocka 2.0 comes to the planet Quatros, where a distress signal from the professor Aldous Witch has originated. It turns out to be a trap, set by super-powered Witch in order to trap some heroes and steal their ship.
name: Savage Planet

description: Conclusion of the Savage Planet plot - the heroes prevail and defeat the Witch Doctor, restoring Quatros to its original state.
name: Savage Planet 2

description:
Norman Osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R. return! Witness the new Avengers line-up in action!

Note: The cover is a homage to the classic recruitment poster sporting Uncle Sam!

Miles Morales is the new Spider-Man! What’s the secret behind his powers, and how will he master them? What new and familiar enemies will rise to challenge this all-new Spider-Man? The most-talked about story of the year keeps delivering the shocking surprises!
name: What Would Peter Do?

description: The Panther vs. The Kingpin...the battle begins! With Daredevil out of Hell’s Kitchen, The Hand’s new leader makes his move for ultimate power. But why is Wilson Fisk targeting Wakandan citizens…and can T’Challa save the one woman who holds the key to unlocking the Kingpin’s plans from the deadly aim of Lady Bullseye and Typhoid Mary? Ever since T’Challa agreed to take over for DD, you knew this war was coming…here it is!
name: The Kingpin of Wakanda

volume.name: Black Panther: The Most Dangerous Man Alive

description: The explanation of where Marvelman went and his transition to Miracleman.
name: Miracleman: A Dream of Flying

description:
Alan Moore explains the dream-scape in which the Miracleman family were raised in to be much like the dream state of the Red King in Alice in Wonderland. It is believed that the Red King must remain a sleep, since we are all part of his dream and will disappear and cease to exist if he were to wake up. Miracleman is compared to as the Red King, because of him waking up will end the nasty experiments Dr. Gargunza is conducting on the sleeping bodies of the Miracleman Family.

This book also reprints the issue of the birth of Miracleman's daughter Winter Moran. Winter's birth was controversial since it was very detailed and accurate graphic birth in which some retailers considered in pornography and return issue #9 of the original series because of fee of legal issues.
name: Miracleman: The Red King Syndrome

description: Red Hood, Arsenal and Starfire enter the Chamber of All to discover what the Untitled wanted--but they'll need to leave their most cherished memories as collateral. All this as the trio draws ever closer to dealing with a threat that's already killed the ancient caste of assassins who taught Jason Todd everything he knows about the art of killing!
name: Cherish is the Word I Use--to Destroy You!

description:
Dan Dare poster magazine (featuring the Dan Dare from 2000AD) published in 1977.

With a history of the character and giant fold-out poster illustrated by Massimo Belardinelli.
name: Dan Dare poster magazine

description:
Fourth issue reprinting the very first Death Wish episodes from Speed comic (Blake Edmonds story moved to Tiger when Speed was cancelled and finally found a home in Eagle, when the two comics merged in 1985). Art by Vanyo.

  • Death Wish (Speed comic reprints) (art: Vanyo)

Also contains all nine episodes of Manix - in Enemy Hands.

  • Manix: In Enemy Hands (from Eagle issue 100-108) (writer: Alan Grant (writing as Keith Law) - artist: Carmona)
name: Death Wish
